Class AbstractFieldProbe<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.sarl.sre.services.probing.probes.AbstractProbe<T>

    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Probe<T>

    public abstract class AbstractFieldProbe<T>
extends AbstractProbe<T>
    Abstract probe implementation is linked to a field. A probe is thread-safe.

      • sync

        public def sync([forcedReading : boolean],
                [forceIfInactive : boolean]) : void 
        Description copied from interface: Probe
        Force the synchronization of the probed value.

        The synchronization does nothing if the probe is inactive.

        Parameters:
        forcedReading - indicates if the reading of the probed value must be forced from the probed element. By default, the value of this parameter is true.
        forceIfInactive - indicates if the synchronization must be done even if the probe is inactive; By default, the value of this parameter is false.
